  "scale": {
    "_comment": "REALISM RULE: objects are scaled to the world by real height, so they sit correctly next to characters. A character is ~character_height_px tall (the 64px skeleton) representing character_height_m. The loop turns each object's world_height_m into world_px_height = round(world_height_m * character_height_px / character_height_m); a game renders the sprite scaled to that pixel height. So a coin (~0.22m) is tiny next to a character and an oak (~6m) towers. Every object MUST have a world_height_m (per-object, else category_height_m fallback).",
